{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon"

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. Baggages have been unloaded. All passengers have disembarked. The crew has exited the aircraft. Staff wants to clean the cabin passenger seating area using bleach. Is that Ok?", 
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. Baggages have been unloaded. All passengers have disembarked. The crew has exited the aircraft. Staff needs to clean the cabin passenger searing area. Provide cleaning instructions and report cleaning status."
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-4o",
    },
    "instructions_prefix": """
You are in charge of a portion of the cleaning services for an airline turnaround operation.
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise, 
from the company's perspective. 
Only use your tools to answer inquiries. 
Do not try to help for personal matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
""",

    "tools": [
        # This first agent definition is regarded as the "Front Man", which
        # does all the talking to the outside world/client.
        #
        # Some disqualifications from being a front man:
        #   1) Cannot use a CodedTool "class" definition
        #   2) Cannot use a Tool "toolbox" definition
        #
        # Besides the first agent being the front man, these tool definitions
        # do not have to be in any particular order. How they are linked and
        # call each other is defined within their own specs.
        # This could be a graph, potentially even with cycles.

        {
            "name": "aircraft_cleaning_coordinator",
            "function": {
                // "description": """
                // Your name is aircraft cleaning coordinator. You are the main point of contact for all cleaning related inquiries.
                // """,    

                "description": """
                Your name is aircraft_cleaning_coordinator. 
                You are the main point of contact for all cleaning related inquiries.
                You answer inquiries about aircraft cleaning.
                """,

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the passenger disembarkation status."
                        },    
                        "crew_exit_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the crew exit status."
                        },    
                        "baggage_unload_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the baggage unload status."
                        }
                    }, 
                    // "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","gate_id","passenger_disembarkation_status","crew_exit_status","baggage_unload_status"] 
                    "required": ["passenger_disembarkation_status","crew_exit_status","baggage_unload_status"] 
                }             
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the top-level agent responsible for handling all cleaning related inquiries.
Do not make things up. This is not a game.
Store the user input as user_inquiry then proceed as follows: 
1. From user_inquiry, determine
    a. flight number as flight_number
    b. aircraft type as aircraft_type
    c. gate id as gate_id
    d. flight status as flight_status
    e. passenger disembarkation status as passenger_disembarkation_status
    f. crew exit status as crew_exit_status
    g. baggage unload status as baggage_unload_status
2. Check the following statuses:
    a. passenger disembarkation status such as'completed' 
    b. crew exit status such as 'completed' 
    c. baggage unload status such as 'completed' 
3. If passenger_disembarkation_status = 'completed' and crew_exit_status = 'completed' and baggage_unload_status = 'completed' then go to step 6.
4. If passenger_disembarkation_status is not 'completed' and crew_exit_status is not 'completed' and baggage_unload_status is not 'completed' then
    a. call your tools to make sure that passenger_disembarkation_status = 'completed' and crew_exit_status = 'completed' and baggage_unload_status = 'completed'
    b. wait for their responses 
5. Call trackerAPI
    a. wait for its response 
    b. store passenger disembarkation status as passenger_disembarkation_status, store crew exit status as crew_exit_status, and store baggage unload status as baggage_unload_status
    c. If passenger_disembarkation_status is not 'completed' and crew_exit_status is not 'completed' and baggage_unload_status is not 'completed' then, go back to step 4.
6. If passenger_disembarkation_status = 'completed' and crew_exit_status = 'completed' and baggage_unload_status = 'completed' then
    a. call aircraft_cleaning_assistant to get cleaning instructions as final_response. 
    b. Wait for its response and save it as final_response and cabin_cleaning_status
    c. Report cabin_cleaning_status
7. Provide the cleaning report summary as: 
    ** cabin cleaning instructions **: 
    [final_response]
    ** cabin cleaning status summary **: 
    [cabin_cleaning_status]
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            # Specify the sly data that should come back from the tools to the client.
            # The session is initiated by the tool, and the client must re-use it to continue the conversation.
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                        "door_opening_status": true 
                        "crew_debrief_status": true
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true
                        "crew_exit_status": true
                        "baggage_unload_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            # Specify the sly data that should come back from the tools to the client.
            # The session is initiated by the tool, and the client must re-use it to continue the conversation.
            "allow": {
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                        "door_opening_status": true 
                        "crew_debrief_status": true
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true
                        "crew_exit_status": true
                        "baggage_unload_status": true
                    }
                }
            },
            
            # Specify the sly data that should come back from the tools to the client.
            # The session is initiated by the tool, and the client must re-use it to continue the conversation.
            "allow": {
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                        "door_opening_status": true 
                        "crew_debrief_status": true
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true
                        "crew_exit_status": true
                        "baggage_unload_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

#######
            # Specify the sly data that should come back from the tools to the client.
            # The session is initiated by the tool, and the client must re-use it to continue the conversation.
            "allow": {
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_status": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "crew_debrief_status": true
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true
                        "crew_exit_status": true
                        "baggage_unload_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["aircraft_cleaning_assistant","trackerAPI","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_disembark","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_crew_exit","/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_baggage_unload"]
        },

        {
            "name": "aircraft_cleaning_assistant",
            "function": {
                "description": """
                Your name is aircraft_cleaning_assistant. You provide cleaning instructions to 
                staff' questions about aircraft cleaning policies, procedures, and resources that they can access.
                """,       
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the passenger disembarkation status."
                        },    
                        "crew_exit_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the crew exit status."
                        },    
                        "baggage_unload_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the baggage unload status."
                        }
                    }, 
                    // "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","gate_id","passenger_disembarkation_status","crew_exit_status","baggage_unload_status"] 
                    "required": ["passenger_disembarkation_status","crew_exit_status","baggage_unload_status"] 
                }      

            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Your name is aircraft_cleaning_assistant. 
You provide cleaning instructions to 
staff' questions about aircraft cleaning policies, procedures, and resources that they can access.
Use only your tools to answer inquiries.
Report final response as final_response and cabin cleaning status as cabin_cleaning_status.
Do not make things up. This is not a game.

            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools":    ["passenger_seating_area"]
        },

        {
            "name": "passenger_seating_area",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}, 
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
The name of this app is `cabin passenger seating area`. 
Use only your tools to fulfill user inquiry. 
Do not make things up. This is not a game.
Your primary responsibility is to handle user inquiry. 
You find existing operational restrictions. 
You ensure that user inquiry complies with existing operational restrictions. 
Call ALL your downstream agents to see if they can help with the inquiry before answering.
Ensure that inquiry complies with existing operational restriction. 
            """,
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["check_restriction","cleaning_tracker"]
        },

        {
            "name": "check_restriction",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}, 
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Do not make things up. This is not a game.
Use only your tools. 
When you receive user inquiry, proceed in the following order: 
1. Call your tool pull_restriction to find existing operational restriction. 
2. If pull_restriction returns no existing operational restriction: call extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating and return its response to user. 
3. If pull_restriction returns any existing operational restriction: call execution and pass user inquiry and operational restriction that pull_restriction has returned. 
            """,
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": [ "pull_restriction","execution","cleaning_tracker"]
        },

        {
            "name": "pull_restriction",
            "function": {
                "description": """
Find existing operational restriction. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "app_name": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The name of an app, website or tool"
                        },
                        "restriction_applies": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The determination if restriction applies"
                        },
                        "restriction_on_cleaning": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The restriction on cleaning"
                        },
                        "user_inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user inquiry"
                        },
                    },
                    "required": ["app_name"]
                }
            },
            "class": "extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating.pull_restriction"
        },

// ### Morning version of execution agent prior to discussion with Dan and modification
//         {
//             "name": "execution",
//             "function": ${aaosa_call}, 
//             "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
// You are the execution agent. 
// You propare the response to user inquiry. 
// 1. Evaluate that user inquiry complies with existing operational restrictions. 
// 2. If compliant, Call extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating. Return the response to the user. 
// 3. If not compliant
//     a. Ask the user exactly this question and WAIT for the answer: 
//         "Your request does not comply with restriction on cleaning. Would you like me to propose a compliant process? (yes/no)" 
//     b. When the user replies, make sure that their response be exactly "yes" or "no". 
//         - If response is "yes": Call extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating. Return the response to the user. 
//         - If response is "no": Call create_escalation. Return the response to the user. 
//             """,
//             "command": ${aaosa_command},
//             "tools": [ "create_escalation","extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating","cleaning_tracker"]
//         },

### Afternoon version of execution agent after discussion with Dan and modification
        {
            "name": "execution",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I check that user inquiry complies with restriction_on_cleaning. 
I make recommendation to user about alternate procedure when their inquiry does not comply with restriction_on_cleaning.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "Inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user inquiry"
                        },
                        "restriction_on_cleaning": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The restriction on cleaning"
                        },
                    },
                    "required": ["Inquiry","restriction_on_cleaning"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """
You are the execution agent. 
You prepare the response to user inquiry when there is operational restriction. 
You receive existing operational restriction from check_restriction. 
1. Determine if user inquiry complies with existing operational restriction that you have received from check_restriction. 
2. If user inquiry complies: Call extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating and return its response to the user. 
3. If user inquiry does not comply: 
    a. Ask the user exactly this question and WAIT for the answer: "Your inquiry does not comply with restriction on cleaning. Would you like me to propose a compliant process? (yes/no)" 
    b. Wait for the user response
    c. When the user replies, make sure that their response is exactly "yes" or "no". 
        - If user response is "no": call escalation_agent and return the response to user. 
        - If user response is "yes": call extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating to create an escalation. Return the response to user. 
            """,
            // "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": [ "escalation_agent","extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating","cleaning_tracker"]
        },

// ${instructions_prefix} 

        {
            "name": "escalation_agent",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}, 
//             "function": {
//                 "description": """
// I create an escalation when user response to proposed compliant cleaning process is "no". 
//                 """,
//                 "parameters": {
//                     "type": "object",
//                     "properties": {
//                         "Inquiry": {
//                             "type": "string",
//                             "description": "The user inquiry"
//                         },
//                         "restriction_on_cleaning": {
//                             "type": "string",
//                             "description": "The restriction on cleaning"
//                         },
//                     },
//                     "required": ["Inquiry","restriction_on_cleaning"]
//                 }
//             },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You responsibility is to create escalation. 
Return result. 
            """,
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["create_escalation"]
        },

// Do not make things up. This is not a game.
// Use only your tools. 
// When you receive a request, call your tool to create an escalation. 

        {
            "name": "create_escalation",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent creates escalation.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "app_name": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The name of an app, website or tool"
                        },
                        "restriction_on_cleaning": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "This is the restriction on cleaning"
                        },
                        "restriction_applies": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "This tells whether or not restriction applies to user inquiry. "
                        },
                        "response_to_recommendation": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user response to the suggestion that could be either positive or negative."
                        },
                        "user_inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user inquiry text"
                        },
                    },
                    // "required": ["app_name","response_to_recommendation"]
                }
            },
            "class": "extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating.create_escalation"
        },

// "restriction_on_cleaning","restriction_applies",

        {
            "name": "extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating",
            "function": {
                "description": """

This agent returns the text contents of operational procedures when user inquiry complies with operational restriction or when the user response to execution agent question is "yes". 
It returns the text content of the escalation message.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "app_name": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The name of an app, website or tool"
                        },
                        "response_to_recommendation": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user response to recommendation."
                        },
                        "restriction_applies": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The determination of restricton applicability."
                        },
                        "restriction_on_cleaning": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The restriction on cleaning."
                        },
                        "user_inquiry_compliant": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user inquiry compliance status."
                        },
                        "user_inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user inquiry text"
                        },
                    },
                    "required": ["app_name"]
                }
            },
            "class": "extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating.ExtractDocs"
        },

        {
            "name": "cleaning_tracker",
            "function": {
                "description": """
Store and track parameters and states of the cleaning process. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "app_name": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The name of an app, website or tool"
                        },
                        "restriction_on_cleaning": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The restriction on cleaning"
                        },
                        "escalation_on_cleaning": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The escalation on cleaning"
                        },
                        "restriction_applies": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user requesrt restraction status"
                        },
                        "response_to_recommendation": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user response toi recommendation"
                        },
                        "user_inquiry_compliant": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user inquiry compliance to restriction on cleaning"
                        },
                        "user_inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The user inquiry text"
                        },
                    },
                    // "required": ["app_name","restriction_on_cleaning"]
                }
            },
            "class": "extract_docs_cabin_passenger_seating.cleaning_tracker"
        },

#########
        {
            "name": "trackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
I check jetbridge connection status as jetbridge_connection_status. 
I check door opening status as door_opening_status. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "ground_services_request_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the inquiry received for grand services."
                        },         
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks installation status."
                        },   
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu readiness status."
                        },     
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the acu connection status."
                        },     
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gpu connection status."
                        },     

                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the engines stop status."
                        },    
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the jetbridge connection status."
                        },    
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },    
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the passenger disembarkation status."
                        },    
                        "crew_debrief_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the crew debrief status."
                        },    
                        "crew_exit_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the crew exit status."
                        },    
                    }, 
                    // "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","flight_status","assigned_runway_id","gate_id","ground_services_request_type"] 
                }
            },
            "class": "aircraft_cleaning.trackerAPI" 
        }, 
#########
    ]
}
